    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-05-10T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-05-10T18:00:00-05:00" n="599"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d599">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.56386A/5–951: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Saudi Arabia</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d599fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_JGL1"
                            >Jones</persName> and <persName>Awalt</persName>; telegraphic
                        transmission and classification approved by <persName corresp="#p_JGL1"
                            >Jones</persName>; cleared with <persName corresp="#p_HGA1"
                            >Haselton</persName>, <gloss target="#t_NEA1">NEA</gloss>, and <persName
                            corresp="#p_SIS1">Silver</persName>, S/<gloss target="#t_ISA1"
                            >ISA</gloss>; and discussed with <persName corresp="#p_PCG1"
                            >Patrick</persName> of Defense.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-05-10T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 10, 1951—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>380. Re <gloss target="#t_DAF1">DAF</gloss> Dept informing <persName
                        corresp="#p_GDA1">Greenhill</persName>, Brit Emb, Gen <persName
                        corresp="#p_DEM1">Day</persName> recalled recently for quick briefing
                    session. <persName corresp="#p_DEM1">Day</persName> now rejoining <gloss
                        target="#t_Amb1">Amb</gloss>
                    <persName corresp="#p_HRA1">Hare</persName> for resumption negots early date and
                    effort obtain agreement quickly. Importance <gloss target="#t_DAF1">DAF</gloss>
                    increasing in US strategic consideration.… Initial effort seek long term
                    agreement defeated largely owing impact Anglo-Egyptian differences<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d599fn2">For documentation on this subject, see <ref
                            target="#pg_343">pp. 343</ref> ff.</note> on <gloss target="#t_SA2"
                        >SA</gloss> sensibilities and as consequence US prepared accept much shorter
                    term. Negots entering very delicate and we hope final stage and we trust Brit
                    will say or do nothing rock boat this period.</p>
                <p>Brit informed here gen character and magnitude proposed <gloss target="#t_NE1"
                        >NE</gloss> mil grant aid program (<gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss>
                    655, May 9<note n="3" xml:id="d599fn3">Not printed; it requested guidance “re
                        extent to which Brit informed nature contemplated conversations on <gloss
                            target="#t_DAF1">DAF</gloss> and military assistance with particular
                        reference possible grant mil assistance <gloss target="#t_NE1">NE</gloss>
                        countries.” (711.56386A/5–951)</note>) of approx $40,000,000. Brit also told
                        <gloss target="#t_SA2">SA</gloss> wld be recipient largest share owing US
                    special interests, but amount left vague.</p>
                <p>Dept hopes conduct in conjunction def mil-polit conversations with Brit re whole
                    program for <gloss target="#t_NE1">NE</gloss> soon in accordance basic <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>
                    <pb facs="1093" n="1053" xml:id="pg_1053"/> paper on subj which contemplates
                    correlated US–UK action re mil assistance to area.<note n="4" xml:id="d599fn4"
                        >For documentation on this subject, see <ref target="#pg_1">pp. 1</ref>
                        ff.</note>
                </p>
                <p>You may discuss with <persName corresp="#p_TAC1">Trott</persName> along above
                    lines ur discretion.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Comment:</hi> Dept doubts <persName corresp="#p_TAC1"
                        >Trott</persName> informed thus far by <gloss target="#t_FonOff1"
                        >FonOff</gloss>, but fol US–UK talks <gloss target="#t_FonOff1"
                        >FonOff</gloss> will presumably circularize Brit <gloss target="#t_NE1"
                        >NE</gloss> missions topsec basis.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
